  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Parkinson's disease is diagnosed clinically, because biomarkers that may help in diagnosis
      and differential diagnosis are not yet available. Exhaled breath testing may yield a
      &quot;breath-print&quot; that can be used to distinguish healthy and diseased states.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
